layerItems.description:
OpenEmbedded-Core is a layer containing the core metadata for current versions
of OpenEmbedded. It is distro-less (can build a functional image with
DISTRO = "nodistro") and contains only emulated machine support.
layerItems.name: openembedded-core

layerItems.description: This layer provides support for using Xilinx tools on supported architectures MicroBlaze, Zynq and ZynqMP.
layerItems.name: meta-xilinx-tools
layerItems.summary: This layer provides support for using Xilinx tools on supported architectures MicroBlaze, Zynq and ZynqMP.

layerItems.description:
This layer is meant to augment Yocto/OE functionality to provide a
Baremetal/Standalone Toolchain as well as a generic version of various
firmware that is required to boot a ZynqMP or Versal system.

For optimized versions of the firmware and additional components you must
use the meta-xilinx-tools layer.
layerItems.name: meta-xilinx-standalone
layerItems.summary: This layer provides a Baremetal/Standalone Toolchain as well as a generic version of various firmware that is required to boot a ZynqMP or Versal system.

layerItems.description: This layer provides support for MicroBlaze, Zynq and ZynqMP.
layerItems.name: meta-xilinx-core
layerItems.summary: This layer provides support for MicroBlaze, Zynq and ZynqMP.
